  "HeaderCoreAreaLink" -> {}, 
  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 57, 5.755523}", 
    "history" -> {"14.2", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"quantum natural gradient"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "QuantumGeometricTensor[vec, {x1, x2, ...}] returns the quantum geometric \
tensor for the state vector vec parametrized with parameters {x1, x2, ...}. \
QuantumGeometricTensor[vec, {x1, x2, ...}, {a1, a2, ...}] returns the quantum \
geometric tensor at x1 = a1, x2 = a2, .... QuantumGeometricTensor[{m1, m2, \
..., mg}, vec] returns the g*g quantum geometric tensor at state vector vec \
that is parametrized through the mutually commuting Hermitian generators m1, \
m2, ..., mg and evaluated at certain values of g parameters. \
QuantumGeometricTensor[{m1, m2, ..., mg}, {v1, v2, ..., vl}] assumes that all \
l parameterized quantum circuit (PQC) layers have the same gates generated by \
{m1, m2, ..., mg} (and a possibly additional sublayer of non-parametrized \
gates), and returns the block-diagonal approximate (g l)*(g l) quantum \
geometric tensor at state vector vl, calculating the k^th block at state \
vector vk. QuantumGeometricTensor[{{m11, m12, ...}, {m21, m22, ...}, ...}, \
{v1, v2, ..., vl}] assumes that the parameterization parts of the PQC layers \
are cyclically repeated and are characterized by the corresponding sets of \
Hermitian generators. QuantumGeometricTensor[gnr] represents the operator \
form of QuantumGeometricTensor operating on vectors or list of vectors, where \
gnr may be a one- or two-dimensional arrays of Hermitian matrices \
(generators).", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "QuantumGeometricTensor", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
    "windowtitle" -> "QuantumGeometricTensor", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/QuantumGeometricTensor"}},
